<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Washington Naval Arms Conference of 1921-1922 achieved:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">A permanent end to naval competition</option>
            <option letter="b">The Five-Power Treaty limiting naval armaments</option>
            <option letter="c">A military alliance against Germany</option>
            <option letter="d">Increased naval spending</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Washington Naval Conference resulted in the Five-Power Treaty, which established a 5:5:3:1.75:1.75 ratio of naval strength between the United States, Britain, Japan, France, and Italy respectively. This agreement temporarily limited naval armaments and helped reduce military spending among major powers. The conference represented a significant diplomatic effort to prevent a naval arms race in the post-WWI period.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
